Chinese Delegation Pays Homage to Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- The Chinese delegation of martyr Mao Anying's family and relatives headed by former Deputy Department Director of the Chinese Academy of Military Science Shao Hua visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace on Sunday to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung.
 The guests made a bow to him who lies in state, with boundless reverence for him.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they went round with deep emotion orders, medals and certificates of honorary titles he was awarded in Korea and foreign countries, the mourning hall which recalls visitors to those days when the Korean people were shedding bitter tears over the greatest loss of the nation, a train coach and a car he used for on-the-spot guidance and foreign tour and in the last period of his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head of the delegation wrote in the visitor's book that the President will live forever.

U.S. Urged to Take Hands off Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- The Swiss Committee for Supporting the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea in a statement on May 1 demanded the United States take its hands off Korea and Yankees withdraw from south Korea at once.
 The warmonger Bush group is considering socialist Korea to be a thorn in its flesh, the statement said, noting it is because the U.S. imperialists sustained a bitter defeat in Korea for the first time in history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists have militarily occupied the southern part of the Korean Peninsula for over 60 years, contrary to the will of the Korean people, it said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. forces in south Korea are the very one responsible for the division of the Korean nation and the main obstacle to Korea's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists' moves to ignite a new war of aggression are being foiled by the might of the Songun politics of leader  Kim Jong Il who is giving a definite priority to military affairs.

Hanchongryon Calls for Concerted Efforts to Build Reunified Country 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Hwang Yu Sok, chairman of the National Reunification Committee of the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon), reportedly published an appeal on May 6, which called upon the students to take the lead in the movement for the reunification of the country.
 Urging them to display their enthusiasm in the van of the reunification movement to make a considerable contribution to the peace and reunification of the country, the appeal said: Hanchongryon, the vanguard of the reunification movement, should rouse more students to play a proper role in the struggle for independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should make the June 15 festival this year an arena overflowing with the sentiments for independent reunification, peace against war and great national unity and an arena giving full scope to the will and stamina in achieving independent reunification at any cost with the concerted efforts of our nation, holding high the banner of "By our nation itself", the appeal said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Reunification is aimed at building a society where the whole nation would live in happiness. So, all of us should rise up vigorously to achieve it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Hanchongryon should turn out in building a reunified country, coordinating steps.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Monday dedicates  a signed  article  to the 18th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's famous work "Let Us All Live and Struggle Like Heroes".
 The work published on May 15, Juche 77 (1988) clarifies valuable truth that to live and struggle like heroes means leading  the most worthwhile and rewarding life as an independent human being and principled issues of making the spirit of heroic struggle prevail throughout the society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last nearly 20 years since the publication of the work have witnessed great heroism displayed in the confrontation with the imperialists and the United States and the drive to build a great prosperous powerful nation in the DPRK, world startling heroic feats performed by its army and people and the stirring reality in which everybody lives and struggles like a hero, all of which is ascribable to Kim Jong Il's outstanding idea and his wise leadership, the article notes, and says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A new great surge will be effected in this land when all the servicepersons and people fully display mass heroism in the on-going general march of Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Working hard to accomplish the cause of Songun of the Workers' Party of Korea, in particular, means a main engine for performing ceaseless heroic feats in the on-going sacred struggle to defend and glorify Korean-style socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mass heroism now being fully displayed among the servicepersons and people in the general march of Songun revolution is based on their conviction of victory in the cause of Songun. "Let us meet the requirements of Songun in the ideological view, the fighting trait and lifestyle!" is the maxim of the servicepersons and people in their struggle and life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are registering signal successes in their drive to build a great prosperous powerful nation in all fields and at all units with a high caliber and innovative insight. They are, at the same time, carrying out their tasks, remaining true at their posts of the revolution with pure conscience and sense of obligation that one should deem it an honor to have joy and sorrow and an ordeal on the road of following the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will become richer and more powerful as the days go by thanks to the heroic people who are dedicating themselves to Kim Jong Il with pure conscience and noble sense of obligation, the article concludes.

Nuclear Warmongers' Reckless Moves under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- The United States' escalated moves to update nuclear weapons and develop laser weapons are dangerous and reckless war moves to establish military domination over the world, observes Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. bellicose forces, not content with the nukes stockpiled by them, are now stepping up the development and production of new type nukes in real earnest, while busying themselves developing laser weapons for starting a space war. This is aimed at retaining a military monopoly and dominating the world with nuclear and other sophisticated weapons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said moves and other reckless war scenarios of the U.S imperialists are unpardonable criminal acts as they disturb the world peace and stability, strain the international situation and spark off a new nuclear arms race. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation still remains tense on the Korean Peninsula due to these moves for a nuclear war. It is their unchangeable scenario to ignite a nuclear war in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are staging frequent nuclear war maneuvers after massively deploying nuclear strike means in south Korea and in its vicinity, posing a grave threat to the DPRK. It is not hard to guess which country their new type nuclear and laser weapons target against. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. bellicose forces' moves to deliberately coil up the military tension on the peninsula and increase the danger of a nuclear war cannot but arouse vigilance among its neighboring countries. It is clear to everyone that in case a nuclear war breaks in Korea what disastrous consequences it will bring. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. would be well advised to give up its criminal design to update nuclear weapons, militarize the outer space and impose a nuclear disaster upon humankind.

National Pride, Vitalizer for Independent Reunification Movement 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- The national pride of the Koreans is a vitalizer which instills vigor into the ranks of the movement for the independent reunification of the country and braces up their patriotic zeal, says Rodong Sinmun in an article Monday.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pride of the Korean nation rooted in superior national character which it can boast to the world is higher than that of any other nation. The Koreans can pave the way for independent reunification and heyday of prosperity of the country when all of them struggle with such national pride and patriotic mettle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pride of the Korean nation is the source of the spirit of independence in the whole course of the reunification movement and the main factor of powerful impetus to the process of great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Independence is as precious as life and soul in the reunification movement of the Korean nation for achieving the nation's independence on a nation-wide scale. A strong wall protecting the nation is built and an upswing is brought in the movement for national reunification when a full scope is given to the unswerving spirit of independence for solving all problems from the stand of giving priority to the nation and displaying Korean nation-first spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The spirit of "By our nation itself" represents the immovable truth that real reconciliation and unity is achieved and the cause of independent reunification is accomplished when all the fellow countrymen struggle with the pride and honor of a homogeneous nation. The last-ditch wriggle of the separatist forces and the strong-arm tactics, arbitrary practices and moves for aggression of the "only super power" prove impotent in face of the torrential flow of history in which the 70 million Koreans are advancing, united in single mind, along the way indicated by the spirit of "By our nation itself".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National pride has a great effect on mental and moral traits of the members of the nation in the struggle for the reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their noble traits in their efforts to shape the destiny of the nation by themselves with confidence and vigor can make even a nuclear weapon impotent. 
 All the fellow countrymen are dynamically waging the worthy patriotic struggle for national reunification to implement the June 15 joint declaration with unshakable fighting spirit and grit, convinced that no force on earth can break the united strength of the Korean nation.

Expansion of U.S. Military Base Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Religionists of four religious orders in south Korea reportedly held a joint prayer meeting in Taechu-ri, Phaengsong Township, Phyongthaek City, on May 11 to denounce the "government" for its moves to expand the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek.
 They called on all the people to turn out in the struggle to make the Hwangsaeul plain a land of life and peace, demanding the punishment of the forces which requisitioned land in Phyongthaek. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Before the meeting, they staged a protest, fighting undauntedly the police blocking their way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earlier, on May 4, the south Korean Writers Council for National Literature issued a statement accusing the "government" authorities of pitching hard to expand the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek designed for the preparation of a war of aggression, following the plan of "strategic flexibility" of the U.S. forces in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the "government" authorities brought the military and police forces into action for a harsh crackdown upon the people fighting against the expansion of the base, the statement said the "government" authorities should no more follow the lead of the U.S.

South Korean Students Vow to Mark June 15 as Day of "By Our Nation Itself"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- The delegation of the south side, which participated in the conference of student representatives from the north and the south of Korea for the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration held at Mt. Kumgang resort, reportedly had a press conference in Maroni Park on a university road in Seoul on May 12.
 At the press conference the delegation said it would conduct a massive movement for commemorating June 15 as the day of "By our nation itself" together with all students and hold a successful grand festival for national reunification to commemorate the 6th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It underlined the need for students to conduct a brisk movement for boosting national cooperation to achieve reunification during the Jun. 13-Aug. 15 period of the joint movement for independent and peaceful reunification, hold a student festival for reunification on the occasion of August 15 and strengthen solidarity and exchange between the students of the south and the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the press conference, the members of the delegation conducted a signature campaign among Seoul citizens with a view to commemorating the day of the publication of the joint declaration as the day of "By our nation itself".

Labor Upsurge Being Effected in Spirit of Wartime Munitions Production 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- The people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea are effecting innovations in all the sectors of the socialist economic construction in the Kunjari spirit.
 The spirit was created by the workers of a munitions factory in Kunjari who produced weapons and ammunitions in time and thus made a great contribution to the victory in the past Fatherland Liberation War. It is run through with the unswerving spirit of guarding the leader with their very lives and the spirit of self-reliance, hard-working, self-sacrifice and revolutionary optimism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung called upon the people to direct every effort to the victory in the war. In response to this call, the workers there manufactured munitions by turning machines manually in water-dripping dead pits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the strategic temporary retreat, the President assigned to the workers there an urgent task of assembling submachine guns for an army unit. Eating parched maize as meals, the 20-member death-defying squad of the factory worked hard day and night and tested the efficiency of weapons by lighting the target with torch, thus assembling 750 submachine guns within six days. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The workers lived an optimistic life, singing revolutionary songs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The common knowledge that the stock of rifle should be made only with white birch tree was also broken by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first Labor Hero in the field of munitions industry was produced out of the workers and the first study-while-working college was founded at the factory during the war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Kunjari spirit is being given fuller play in the Songun era, inspiring the people to labor feats.

Huichon Hard Glassware Factory
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- The Huichon Hard Glassware Factory is associated with the great care shown by the Workers' Party of Korea for the improvement of the living standard of the people.
 The factory situated in Huichon city, Jagang Province was commissioned in November Juche93 (2004). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, with floorage of over 5,230 square meters, is equipped with high-tech facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general control room observes and controls the operation of facilities including glass fusion furnace, press plastic machine, centrifugal plastic machine, automatic controller of voltage and frequency and storage and mixture of raw materials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The hexagon glass fusion furnace, based on electric heating system, has cold water supplying system to cool off the electrodes and a blower to cool off the furnace wall. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The factory produces various kinds of glassware for home use. They are supplied to households in Pyongyang, Jagang Province and other parts of the country.

9th Pyongyang Spring International Trade Fair Opens
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- The 9th Pyongyang Spring International Trade Fair opened at the Three-Revolution Exhibition on Monday.
 Present at the opening ceremony were Vice-Premier of the Cabinet Ro Tu Chol, Minister of Foreign Trade Rim Kyong Man, Chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee Ryang Man Gil, officials concerned and delegations from the DPRK and different countries and regions participating in the fair. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on hand were the Syrian government economic delegation headed by Minister of Economy and Commerce Amer Hosni Lutfi, the delegation of the China Council for the Promotion of International Trade and the Chamber of International Commerce led by Chairman Wan Jifei, and diplomatic representatives and staff members of the foreign embassies here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade Jo Jong Ho in his congratulatory speech said that the fair would mark a significant occasion in developing the friendship and cooperation among different countries and their peoples in conformity with the desire and wishes of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Director of the Korean International Exhibition Corporation Kim Tong Myong in his opening address said that the fair would help boost the friendly and cooperative relations among countries and contribute to satisfactorily conducting multi-faced exchange, cooperation and foreign trade. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will as ever strive to boost the economic exchange and cooperation with all countries friendly towards it, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants laid bouquets before a photograph of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il standing together, displayed at the exhibition hall, before paying tribute to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They looked round various exhibits including steel products, machine tools, poultry equipment, medicines, agricultural chemicals and chemical fertilizers, petrochemicals, electric and electronic products, foodstuff and a variety of daily necessities from companies of the DPRK, China, Syria, Thailand, Spain, Sweden, France, the Czech Republic, Switzerland, Germany, Italy, Netherlands and Taipei of China.

Kim Il Chol Meets Chinese Delegation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Vice Marshal of the Korean People's Army Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, Monday met and conversed in a warm atmosphere with the delegation of martyr Mao Anying's family and relatives led by former Deputy Department Director of the Chinese Academy of Military Science Shao Hua. The delegation has come to Korea to visit the grave of Mao Anying who is son of Chairman Mao Zedong, the great leader of the Chinese people, and fell in the Korean war.
 On the occasion the head of the delegation referred to the China-Korea friendly relations provided by Chairman Mao Zedong and President Kim Il Sung, No one can break these relations between the armies and peoples of the two countries sealed in blood, she noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She expressed thanks to General Secretary Kim Jong Il for having paid deep attention to them during their stay. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were KPA General Pak Jae Gyong, Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Yong Il, Chinese Ambassador to the DPRK Wu Donghe and Military Attache of the Chinese embassy Yang Xilian.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Syrian Government Economic Delegation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a friendly talk with the Syrian government economic delegation led by Minister of Economy and Commerce Amer Hosni Lutfi at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Monday.
 On the occasion the head of the delegation said that during his visit he deeply felt that Korea is a very beautiful country and the Korean people are strong in independence and nationality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that he would make positive efforts to strengthen economic cooperation and exchange between Syria and the DPRK in conformity with the intention of the top leaders of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were DPRK Minister of Foreign Trade Rim Kyong Man and officials concerned and Syrian Charge d'Affaires ad Interim in Pyongyang Muhammad Adib Al Hani.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Chinese Delegation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Monday met and conversed with the delegation of martyr Mao Anying's family and relatives led by former Deputy Department Director of the Chinese Academy of Military Science Shao Hua at the Mansudae Assembly Hall. The delegation has come to Korea to visit the grave of Mao Anying who is son of Chairman Mao Zedong, the great leader of the Chinese people, and fell in the Korean war.
 On hand were Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Yong Il, Chinese Ambassador to the DPRK Wu Donghe and Military Attache Yang Xilian and staff members of the Chinese embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the occasion Kim Yong Nam said that the Chinese party and government organized the volunteers with fine sons and daughters of the Chinese people and dispatched them to the Korean front when the Korean people were undergoing the grimmest ordeals. The Korean people will always remember the feats performed by the martyrs of the Chinese People's Volunteers in the Korean war, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korea-China friendly relations provided by the leaders of the old generation of the two countries are growing stronger under the deep care of leader Kim Jong Il and President Hu Jintao, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Shao Hua expressed heartfelt thanks to Kim Jong Il for having paid particular attention to their visit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that the CPV participated in the Korean war under the banner of "resisting America and aiding Korea, safeguarding the home and defending the motherland", she said that she came to Korea together with children of fallen fighters so as to make them know how precious is the blood shed by their predecessors.

Ro To Chol Meets Chinese Delegations
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the DPRK Cabinet, met and had a friendly conversation with the delegation of the China Development Bank led by its governor Chen Won at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Monday. 
 The head of the delegation said that the friendly and cooperative relations between China and the DPRK have long historical roots, adding that they would make positive efforts to boost these ties provided by revolutionaries of the elder generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Kim Chon Gyun, director of the Central Bank and officials concerned and Wu Shumin, minister councilor of the Chinese embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day Ro also met and had a friendly conversation with the delegation of the China Council for the Promotion of International Trade and the Chamber of International Commerce led by Chairman Wan Jifei at the Mansudae Assembly Hall. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head of the delegation noted that during the visit they were deeply impressed by the endeavors of the Korean people to build a great prosperous powerful nation under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il. The friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries are growing stronger as the days go by under the deep care of President Hu Jintao and leader Kim Jong Il, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade Jo Jong Ho, Director of the Chamber of Commerce of the DPRK Ri Hak Gwon, and Minister Councilor Guan Huabing and Economic and Commercial Councilor Gu Jinsheng of the Chinese embassy here.

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Navy Sub-Unit
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, inspected a sub-unit of Unit 155 of the KPA Navy honored with the title of O Jung Hup-led seventh regiment.
 He acquainted himself with the training of seamen.
 He was satisfied to learn that all the seamen of the sub-unit have firmly prepared themselves to be a-match-for-a hundred stalwart fighters who are well versed in combat and technical equipment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our socialist country is like an impregnable fortress as the ranks of the brave seamen are standing firm guard over the seas of the country, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave them a pair of binoculars and an automatic rifle as gifts and had a photo session with them, expressing the expectation and belief that they would perform exploits as the defenders of the seas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Hwang Pyong So, vice department director of the WPK Central Committee.
